article.headline: N. Iowa 83, Wartburg 61
article.story: CEDAR FALLS, Iowa (AP) -- Adam Viet scored 16 points and Grant Stout added 12 points and seven rebounds to help Northern Iowa to a 83-61 win over Wartburg Wednesday night. Northern Iowa (9-2) had four players in double figures, including Viet and Stout. Eric Coleman also had 12 points, and Jared Josten added 11 for the Panthers. Wartburg (4-4) was led by Nick Gullickson who scored 24 in the losing effort. Lee Nelson also added 16 points and four rebounds for the Knights. Three point shooting was a big factor for Northern Iowa, which went 15-26 from behind the arc, including 5-7 from Viet. Northern Iowa controlled the tempo of the game, and Wartburg never looked a threat to knock off the Panthers, who led 46-27 at the end of the first half.
